      <section>
        <h4 id="scroll-link-1">
          <%= link_to 'Gweepi Medical', 'http://www.gweepi.com/' %>
        </h4>
        <p>I was hired to take over server and mobile development at
        this early-stage healthcare startup. The mobile app would collect
        patient and care data and feed it into the server for analytics and tracking.
        </p>
        <p>The original application architecture was for a single tenant, meaning
        that new customers would require a new application instance and database.
        The team realized that this wasn't ideal for scaling,
        so I planned and executed a migration to a multitenanted architecture
        built with <%= link_to 'Apartment', 'https://github.com/influitive/apartment' %>.
        </p>
        <p>One of the challenges of being the sole (or primary) developer
        in a young company is building reliable software that can respond to
        business changes relatively easily and quickly.
        I had very good success incorporating an
        <%= link_to 'outside-in testing approach',
          'https://robots.thoughtbot.com/testing-from-the-outsidein'%> based very much
          on ideas and processes learned from thoughtbot's Upcase project. A robust
          test suite built confidence in our system's reliability and also made
          a few large refactors to the application architecture easier.
        </p>
        <p>Gweepi worked primary remotely, and I was very lucky to spend
        the winters of 2015 and 2016 working from lovely Honolulu. I really
        enjoyed the challenges and pace of the work, as well as the trust
        and independance that I was given. Ultimately, the product failed to gain
        enough adoption to continue development, despite great feedback and
        reviews from its users.</p>
      </section>
