      </section>
      <section>
        <h4 id="scroll-link-3">
          <%= link_to 'Seoul Web Design', 'www.seoulwebdesign.com' %>
        </h4>
        <p>My first real development work was porting the music site
        <%= link_to 'DoIndie', 'doindie.co.kr' %> from Wordpress to Ruby on Rails.
        The site had plans to add new social network-type features which
        did not seem to be the best fit for Wordpress.
        </p>
        <p>The database migration was done by dumping Wordpress' db to CSV, and
        then importing it to postgres with a rake task. The client and PM were
        concerned about Korean search engine visibility, so I ended up
        provisioning a Korean VPS with chef and deploying with capistrano. The
        <%= link_to 'Deploying Rails book',
          'https://leanpub.com/deploying_rails_applications'%> was invaluable for
        getting this done!</p>
        <p>In addition to porting the app to a new language, I added several
        new 'social' features like Twitter/facebook login, the ability for users
        to like and follow different artists and venues and integration with
        Google maps for showing regional events.</p>
      </section>
